# Interface Design Rules
# Inspired by: shader.se, awwwards.com/sites_of_the_day
# Standard: Award-level creative frontend. Not a template. Not a component library demo.

---

## The Prime Directive

Every screen must have a signature. One thing that makes it unmistakably itself.
Before writing a single line of code, name it:
"The signature of this UI is: ___________"

If you cannot fill that blank with something specific, you are not ready to build.

---

## Before Writing Any Code

1. Check if `.interface-design/system.md` exists.
   - If YES: load it, state active direction, proceed.
   - If NO: run the Design Direction Checkpoint below.

2. **Design Direction Checkpoint**
   State out loud:
   - The signature (see above)
   - Depth strategy: borders-only / subtle shadows / layered elevation / flat
   - Motion personality: none / subtle / expressive / cinematic
   - Typography role: supporting / structural / dominant / the hero
   - Color temperature: warm / cold / neutral / monochrome + one accent
   - Spatial language: dense / balanced / generous / extreme whitespace
   - The one Awwwards-level site this is most spiritually similar to

   Wait for "y" before writing any code.

3. **Per-component checkpoint**
   Before each new component, state the specific tokens: spacing, type scale,
   depth treatment, motion behavior.

