## Interactions — Every Control Is a Crafted Object

- Buttons are not rectangles with text. They have:
  - A specific height (not auto-height from padding alone)
  - A hover state with motion (scale 1.02–1.04 + color shift)
  - An active/press state (scale 0.97)
  - Optional: magnetic pull toward cursor within 60px radius
- Inputs have a focus state that goes beyond outline: border brightens,
  label lifts, background shifts.
- Links in body text: underline as animation, not decoration.
  Slide-in underline on hover (scaleX from 0 to 1).
- Cursor customization when appropriate: hide default cursor, build a
  custom circle cursor that reacts to hoverable elements.

